    <h2>Background</h2>
    <h3>What is a Typology</h3>
        <p>A sociotechnical typology of scientific work enables researchers to systematically analyze & compare diverse scientific projects. This analysis helps surface commonalities that impact software being produced and used by different domains and organizations. 
        </p>
        <p>The STRUDEL Typology is a tool for categorizing key elements making up scientific projects building and using software products. It is designed to help users identify and compare common activities in scientific work that should be considered when focusing on user experiences, software sustainability, and more.
        </p>
